# How to Install Docker on CentOS 8 #


Step 1-) Enable Docker CE Repository 


dnf config-manager --add-repo=https://download.docker.com/linux/centos/docker-ce.repo


Step 2-) Install Docker CE using dnf command


dnf list docker-ce


Step 3-) Now, use beneath dnf command to install latest version of docker,


dnf install docker-ce --nobest -y


Step 4-) After the installation of docker, start and enable its service using the following systemctl commands,


systemctl start docker
systemctl restart docker


Step 5-) Run the following command to verify installed docker version,


docker --version


Step 6-) Verify and test Docker CE Engine


docker run hello-world



